    Let <fr:tex>X</fr:tex> be a compact Kähler variety (for example, smooth and projective).
    By the holomorphic Poincaré lemma, the de Rham complex <fr:tex>\Omega _X^\bullet </fr:tex> is a resolution of the constant sheaf <fr:tex>\mathbb {C}</fr:tex>.
    We thus have an isomorphism (<fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.2"
href="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.2.xml"
number="1.4.2"></fr:ref>)
    <fr:tex
display="block">       \operatorname {H}^\bullet (X,\mathbb {C})       \sim  \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^\bullet (X,\Omega _X^\bullet )     </fr:tex>
    and the stupid filtration on <fr:tex>\Omega _X^\bullet </fr:tex> (<fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.5"
href="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.5.xml"
number="1.4.5"></fr:ref>) defines the hypercohomology spectral sequence

